comments.content: Biotransformation is the chemical modification (or modifications) made by an organism on a chemical compound. If this modification ends in mineral compounds like CO, NH4+, or HO, the biotransformation is called mineralisation.
This pathway was inferred from Homo sapiens pathway [http://www.wikipathways.org/index.php?title=Pathway:WP702&amp;amp;oldid=29945 WP702(r29945)] with a 57% conversion rate.
